🔍 Parsing & Logic

Iterate Over All Trades:

for rune_name, listings in data["Runes"].items():
    for entry in listings:
        # Access offer side
        offer = rune_name
        seller = entry["seller"]
        qty_offer = entry["quantity"]
        time = entry["updated_at"]

        # Access ask side
        price_list = entry.get("price", [])
        if not price_list:
            continue  # Skip entries with no price

        # Single vs AND trade
        if len(price_list) == 1:
            trade_type = "Single"
        else:
            trade_type = "AND"

        # Do something with the trade...

Filter: All AND Trades

and_trades = []
for rune, entries in data["Runes"].items():
    for entry in entries:
        if entry.get("price") and len(entry["price"]) > 1:
            and_trades.append((rune, entry))

Extract Ask Item Counts (flattened)

from collections import Counter

ask_items = [
    item["name"]
    for listings in data["Runes"].values()
    for entry in listings
    if entry.get("price")
    for item in entry["price"]
]

ask_counter = Counter(ask_items)


⸻

🧠 Notes
	•	Offer is always one rune, defined by the dict key.
	•	Ask can be:
	•	Single-item trade → one object in price list.
	•	AND trade → two or more objects in price list.
	•	Use updated_at for recency filtering.
	•	Use quantity fields to weight value comparisons if needed.

